Welcome to June's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute, Roche and beyond.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F9ZLVNuAgcfnUvqN8V9PE2g&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=AQu%2BvtocixSRxgdvIySXy0QU%2FqmsHnttmadNkfnfWaA%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FBEgyjmdpAj01cEgcVCO1EQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=64zND%2BqbWrJ%2B5mP9CY7ifftocomEW0yuyPwt4qJtl94%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care. 
We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FNmCzDIRT1Shbo8dSB0kt-Q&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=5SSQ9uADYXeO8rfhicLOMLsEVuHekZcXa7DUuN8x4AA%3D&reserved=0).

### Applications Open for Partnership Community Scholar Scheme

**Info and Q&A webinar: 05 July 2023**

**Deadline for applications: 31 July 2023**

We have now opened applications for our Turing-Roche Community Scholar scheme. This year-long scheme open to PhD students will award up to 10 successful applicants a stipend of £3000 to embed themselves within our partnership, attend a relevant conference and undertake a selected, community based project. Please share far and wide! Scheme info, how to register for our information webinar and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F4dwilYBP1fzwy1URhcPaSw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=4FqnGt8XtAnYX2VWQh3FjWtjrKaJCIvAY3s1rfkOOkg%3D&reserved=0).

### Knowledge Share Series Event: Personalised Medicine in the face of multi-scale heterogeneity

**27 June 2023**

Join us for our [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FlNwZpfbEO_381HKfDx5WXg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=zENU3pyCIgNfMZSuYG8%2FTyXR8EUGPbaObjc%2F1mMFnbE%3D&reserved=0). Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and the wider scientific community to share partnership updates and different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

June's event is on the 27th and we'll be hearing from partnership Senior Postdoctoral Research Associate Christopher Banerji on the theme of Personalised Medicine in the face of multi-scale heterogeneity.

You can register for the event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPTNqLWl3dElWZ0F0OC1RYVFIcEtBOEhSNncyT2pVTEJ0bHl5dzlBMi1TbjFBODQ2Qm1VTjFFMnR5WHRfLUtuT3ImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi1jZjA0NGUwNzBmYzc0MWE4OGRhODI5MzQxMDY0MWI5MyZlc2lkPTcxODA0MzU2LTY5MGItZWUxMS04ZjZlLTYwNDViZDBlNjc5NSJ9%2F69wfQ4XNfy5-LQ-20PChyg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ArRfrkuxer1zqi4oislRotmAdoEmtW5GWTOYDRZdRS8%3D&reserved=0) and can catch-up on previous recordings of our events at our [YouTube channel](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F1Q5kgFh1AULYayxoJDFYLA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=J5GNqq%2FacZtMCM1ztzUVQ2BjOCYnYBgCgQwx3bZjhgM%3D&reserved=0).

### Partnership Senior Postdoc Rohan Chakraborty presenting at Medical Image Understanding and Analysis (MIUA) Conference

Rohan Chakraborty, partnership Senior Postdoctoral Research Associate, will be presenting his research on generative AI models for super-resolution of degraded or low quality biomages at the [27th International Conference on Medical Image Understanding and Analysis](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPTNqLWl3dElWZ0F0OC1RYVFIcEtBOEhSNncyT2pVTEJ0bHl5dzlBMi1TbjFBODQ2Qm1VTjFFMnR5WHRfLUtuT3ImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi1jZjA0NGUwNzBmYzc0MWE4OGRhODI5MzQxMDY0MWI5MyZlc2lkPTcxODA0MzU2LTY5MGItZWUxMS04ZjZlLTYwNDViZDBlNjc5NSJ9%2FwbE6nVsz01pV7UOdBgYHKQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ZgvThGqxKVHLkp9hv8dGbQUzJxRmGjemJmkK8OCGpoA%3D&reserved=0) in Aberdeen in July. He is senior author of the submitted research article which applies Generative Clinical AI models to quality enhancement of lung CT images. The article will be published through the Springer Lecture Notes in Computer Science (LNCS) series after the conference. 

### Partnership team write Turing Way chapter on 'Academic-Industry Collaborations' 

The partnership team have written a new chapter on ['Academic-Industry Collaborations'](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FeGQ5MHxUNx6Rhgbau2Ve2w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=zJVdiIVw2sNL%2F7UKRlgC9PYWpwMdu%2B9XEY2dl%2BFiWqE%3D&reserved=0) for the [Turing Way](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPTNqLWl3dElWZ0F0OC1RYVFIcEtBOEhSNncyT2pVTEJ0bHl5dzlBMi1TbjFBODQ2Qm1VTjFFMnR5WHRfLUtuT3ImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi1jZjA0NGUwNzBmYzc0MWE4OGRhODI5MzQxMDY0MWI5MyZlc2lkPTcxODA0MzU2LTY5MGItZWUxMS04ZjZlLTYwNDViZDBlNjc5NSJ9%2FMW541mdE1hHvj5vBhuDh8g&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=%2Bvkh2TMvRt4B5%2FavPT0q8FF3hCQ7MbY3hHosNokfcww%3D&reserved=0), a handbook on how to do reproducible, ethical and collaborative data science. Consisting of an introduction and three subchapters ('Establishing an Academic-Industry Collaboration', 'Community Building in an Academic-Industry Collaboration' and a personal story on 'Community Activities'), the text is based on our experiences as a partnership and aims to be a guide for anyone setting up this kind of collaboration. We would welcome any further input and content from other academic-industry collaborations!

### UK- Italy Trustworthy AI Visiting Researcher Programme

**Deadline for applications: 30 September 2023**

The Turing Institute is collaborating with the Italian Future AI Research Foundation to suppport travel and accommodation for early to mid-career researchers affiliated with a UK university or institution to spend two weeks at an Italian University or research centre to discuss issues around Trustworthy AI. The purpose of the visits will be to enable the development of bilateral and multilateral projects in Trustworthy AI and to bootstrap future collaborations between the two scientific communities. The scheme is particularly inviting proposals around healthcare, defence and security and environment and sustainability. More about the scheme and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FKV0j0cv2uDWK0xO_ZsJycQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=vnoZM59hQzeEda4my4WhzhCm9GbchLEJXOMIXI4rDvU%3D&reserved=0).

### AI with Roche: Rare Disease Open Science Data Challenge

Rare Diseases face significant challenges in diagnosis and treatment and are associated with an unprecedented burden on individuals living with the disease and their caregivers- only 5% of the known 10,000+ rare diseases have an FDA-approved treatment. Roche has formed a collaborative partnership with RARE-X Global Genes with an intent to resolve barriers for patients to responsibly share their data and engage in research. 

[AI with Roche](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F-r6D-uHmnSAEiW4oc-XvWA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=prNrhyLHVpXZKiAbidGWrRqCf75bPicdK4w8tvmpWo8%3D&reserved=0) is happy to announce the launch of a Rare Disease Open Science Data Challenge which is bringing together researchers, clinicians and data scientists alongside patients in an open environment to accelerate scientific discovery. You can find out more and how to join the challenge [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FNClpAC4PbTX8dw0XQNLIcA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265328893857%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=rzsMwDjgujtkP47aL8F36m3t6QmkriHyyOjL6MKIpfk%3D&reserved=0).

### Turing Clinical AI Interest Group Summer School

**Registration deadline: 23 June 2023**

**Summer School Event: 20 July 2023**

The Turing's [Clinical AI Interest Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fjet0U-mXnI9CX6bhZjfTOw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265329050124%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Er%2BhYhZ8DY7CNsbVn%2Bkf0KOj7%2FCpMuOgesFT0ae8lkA%3D&reserved=0) are organising a one day summer school event at the Turing Institute to train clinicians with little or no expertise to work with AI. ### Workshop on Spurious Correlations, Invariance and Stability at the International Conference on Machine Learning

**29 July 2023**

This workshop, being held at International Conference on Machine Learning, will bring together domain experts and researchers to facilitate discussions and forge collaborations on problems with spurious correlations, and instability of machine learning models.\
Models built without accounting for spurious correlations often break when deployed in the wild, despite excellent performance on benchmarks. Extensive work on resolving such problems has sprung up in several communities, including Causality, Algorithmic Fairness and Reliable ML. Yet there is little consensus on best practices, useful formal frameworks, rigorous evaluations of models, and fruitful avenues for the future. The workshop aims to spur progress in all of these aspects. Find out more [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FJT30A3OsDHaEEx6L5oLPKQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265329050124%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=DeuFlIHQB0fvCOuDB%2BZ4qE2S2VycDj19rJS3HhOzS2w%3D&reserved=0).

### Applications open for KQ Labs

**Deadline 10 July 2023**

Run by the Francis Crick Institute and funded by LifeArc, KQ labs is an accelerator programme for exciting early-stage start-ups using data as a core part of their business model to improve human health. The programme is delivered over five months, kicking off in October and culminating in a Demo Day event in March 2024. It includes a three day in-person kick-off at the Crick followed by weekly workshops (delivered virtually), mentoring with subject matter experts, and tailored introductions to key investors and corporates. Each company is given £40k funding in the form of a convertible loan note as part of the programme. Apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F9xAZX5yBCnIWsF5WCdcw0w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265329050124%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=RhvO9YLC3y5mEsojq7RlCQWrRkMIp3IQ6IvlqsmCGQw%3D&reserved=0).

### An in silico FSHD muscle fibre for modelling DUX4 dynamics and predicting the impact of therapy

As mentioned in May's newsletter, [this paper](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FIwJPljHSup3jdj7L3qCR9g&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Cef4165ddb4264f1b3cea08db730b7743%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638230265329050124%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=rTEJR2KamssoQK6eQ0%2FIvvxe0v%2BU6qMZqIAaCvcVrwc%3D&reserved=0) from our Senior Postdoctoral Research Associate Chris Banerji and colleagues has now been published in eLife! The team employ stochastic gene expression and compartment models to understand the heterogeneous distribution of DUX4 (a major facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy [FSHD] therapeutic target) in single cell and single nuclear RNA-sequencing data from FSHD patient muscle cells. This approach led to open-source software for in silico screening of anti-DUX4 therapy in FSHD.
